    <who name="Steffen Pingel">steffen.pingel</who>
    <bug_when>2012-03-08 04:43:56 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>When enter is pressed in the find box the traverse event is processed by the 
FilteredTree and focus is transfered to select the first match. This is the desired behavior but interacts badly with selection of content assist proposals which is also triggered by the enter key.

I tried setting ContentProposalAdapter.setPropagateKeys(false) but that didn&apos;t make a difference. 

I have proposed a different solution here: http://review.mylyn.org/361 . It&apos;s a hack but it works on Linux. David, Sam, can you verify on Windows? Please let me know if you better suggestions how to resolve this.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
